{meta: title I’d Like To Teach The World To Sing}
{meta: artist New Seekers}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I'd like to build a world a home 
And furnish it [D7]with love 
Grow apple trees and [G7]honey bees 
And [F]snow white turtle [C]doves
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I'd like to teach the world to sing
In perfect [D7]harmony
I'd like to hold it [G7]in my arms
And [F]keep it [C]company 
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I'd like to see the world for once
All standing hand [D7]in hand
And hear them echo through [G7]the hills 
For [F]peace throughout the [C]land
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
That’s the song I hear
Let the world song [D7]today
A song of peace [G7]that echo’s on
And [F]never goes [C]away
{end_of_verse}

